# TDD Discipline

Pipeline position: ① design → ② plan → **③ THIS** → ④ review → ⑤ ship | Priority 30

Write the test first. Watch it fail. Write minimal code to pass. No exceptions.

## The Iron Law

**NO PRODUCTION CODE WITHOUT A FAILING TEST FIRST.**

Write code before the test? Delete it. Start over. Don't keep it as "reference." Delete means delete.

**Exceptions** (ask user first): throwaway prototypes ("prototype" / "探索"), generated boilerplate, config files.

## RED-GREEN-REFACTOR

### RED — Write one minimal failing test
- One behavior per test. If name contains "and", split it.
- Real code, not mocks (unless unavoidable).

### Verify RED — Run it, watch it fail
**MANDATORY.** Use `Shell` to run the test. Confirm: fails because feature is missing (not typo errors). Test passes immediately? You're testing existing behavior — fix the test.

### GREEN — Simplest code to pass
- Nothing beyond what the test requires. No refactoring yet. YAGNI.

### Verify GREEN — Run it, watch it pass
**MANDATORY.** Confirm: test passes, all other tests still pass, no warnings. Test fails? Fix the code, not the test.

### REFACTOR — Only after green
Remove duplication, improve names, extract helpers. Keep tests green. Don't add behavior.

## Rationalization Prevention

| Excuse | Reality |
|--------|---------|
| "Too simple to test" | Simple code breaks. Test takes 30 seconds. |
| "I'll test after" | Tests-after = "what does this do?" Tests-first = "what should this do?" |
| "Keep as reference" | You'll adapt it. That's testing after. Delete means delete. |
| "Need to explore first" | Fine. Throw away exploration, then TDD. |
| "Test hard = design unclear" | Hard to test = hard to use. Simplify. |
| "TDD will slow me down" | TDD is faster than debugging. |
| "Just this once" | No exceptions. That's rationalization. |

## Red Flags — Delete Code, Start Over

- Wrote code before test
- Test passes immediately with no changes
- About to say "just this once"
- Wanting to "keep as reference"

## Verification Checklist

- [ ] Every new function/method has a test
- [ ] Watched each test fail before implementing
- [ ] Wrote minimal code to pass each test
- [ ] All tests pass (run via `Shell`)
- [ ] Output clean — also check `ReadLints` for introduced errors
- [ ] Edge cases and error paths covered

Can't check all boxes? You skipped TDD. Start over.
